cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the theory of logic programming and nonmonotonic reasoning, which are topics that are typically covered in the sub-categories of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper's abstract mentions the study of fixed-point semantics, which is a key concept in logic programming, and the paper proposes a new method for providing uniform characterizations of different semantics. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to researchers in the above-mentioned sub-categories.
